## Demo Sequence

1. Observability trace imported into action receipt with source refs, workspace
   state, authority scope, stop reason, and verdict.
2. `pipeline-math++` packet with theorem target, source refs, verifier loop,
   counterexample lane, and formal replay boundary.
3. Source claim to protocol skeleton with workflow runtime, measurement
   placeholder, negative result path, and reviewer objection ledger.

This keeps BuildLang/buildc in the plan as a strategic pillar through the
`ScientificRuntimeReceiptFactory`, while preventing it from swallowing the
whole system shape.

## Boundaries

Pass 0123 does not claim market dominance, solve scientific fields, validate
external video claims, prove incumbent gaps as exclusive, or promote a natural
law. Every uniqueness claim remains `HYPOTHESIS_ONLY`.

